frameDefinitions: After a period in which the Agent has been working on a Goal, the Agent manages to attain it.
An Agent initiates the beginning of an ongoing Activity in which he will be continuously involved. '' 'At the same time, city-states began to grow in influence on the southern Greek mainland.'
A Device or machine is put in (or out of) service either by a volitional Agent or by a Cause event or force acting on the Device.

A  Mitigating_situation is presented as occurring against the backdrop of a more preferable situation and a less preferable situation that, while expected, feared, or hoped for, did not or will not occur; the Mitigating_situation is thus, so to speak, sandwiched between a better and a worse situation, both of which are relevant in the discourse.
An Agent attempts to achieve a Goal using some Means.
An Agent attempts to achieve a Goal.
frameExamples: At the same time, city-states <t>began</t> to grow in influence on the southern Greek mainland.
The laborer realized that he <t>activated</t> the machine but did not know how to stop it.
<t>At least</t> I don’t have to go to school.
John <t>tried</t> using a crowbar to open the door.
listRoleDefinitions: The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs the intentional act that fulfills the <fen>Goal</fen>.
The state or action that the <fen>Agent</fen> has wished to participate in.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> achieves their <fen>Goal</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> achieves their <fen>Goal</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> that an <fen>Agent</fen> starts.
This role identifies the being that starts the intentional <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> starts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> starts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Device</fen> or machine that is in or out of operation.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who changes the operational state of the <fen>Device</fen>.
<fen>Cause</fen> identifies the non-agentive force that causes the <fen>Device</fen> to begin to operate.
The <fen>Time</fen> when a <fen>Device</fen> is put into or out of operation.
The <fen>Place</fen> in which the <fen>Device</fen> is put into or out of operation.

The <fen>Mitigating_situation</fen> is the situation that actually occurs. It is presented in a discourse to mitigate the fact that a better situation did not occur - since the role is still preferable to an even worse situation.
The <fen>Agent</fen> makes an attempt to achieve a <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the <fen>Agent</fen> attempts to achieve.
This role identifies the <fen>Means</fen> by which an attempt occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt occurs.
The place where an attempt is made.
The <fen>Agent</fen> makes an attempt to achieve a <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the <fen>Agent</fen> attempts to achieve.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt occurs.
The place where an attempt is made.
listRoleExamples: Iraq had achieved <fex>its programme objective of producing nuclear weapons</fex> .
<fex>By 1700</fex> , our forces will have achieved total victory .
She had already achieved that feat <fex>in Burma</fex> .
<fex>The night lights</fex> were turned on in the secondary school.
Instantly <fex>Sue</fex> activated the commlink on the wall.
He was in his stocking feet while standing in the bayou that formed when <fex>the wind</fex> turned the shower on in that one upstairs bathroom.
My dad turned the lights on for me <fex>at 10 o'clock</fex>
Suddenly, the lights got turned on <fex>on the Jamaica road bridge</fex>.
We didn't win $7 million, but at least <fex>I only lost $2 on lottery tickets</fex>.
John tried using a crowbar <fex>to enter the locked door</fex>.
<fex>On the bridge</fex> he tried the crowbar.
<fex>On the bridge</fex> he attempted to put the wig on.
